<tr><td colspan=2><ul>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f106245004947851>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=2490&mid=106245004947851>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=2490&mid=106245004947851>RE: Getting up alchemy....</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=2490&mid=106245004947851#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Sep 1st 5:02 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=220288><span id=Scholar>Lord Raksus</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>36 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>First, a word of warning...&nbsp;&nbsp;After spending quite a while researching this, I've found the great majority of shamans are at best disgruntled with alchemy.  Many have spent a fortune and found that only a handful of potions sell, and even then fairly slowly.  The fastest seller is these SoW potions, but you barely make a profit on it.  On most servers you can usually get 10 shots for 70pp.  Considering they cost about 55 to make, after you factor in the failure rate it's a pretty sad profit even with great skill.  On the other hand, stinging wort potions can bring in huge profits.  They require camping ice giants, but you can make them for about 600pp and sell for 1500-2000.  They're horribly unbalanced instant heal potions.  A 52 monk solo'd Nagafen recently with a bunch of these.  Aside from these 2 potions, alchemy can be a very hard sell.  Depends on the server it seems.  I've seen some shaman say they sell a particular potion very quickly, and some others say they've had the same one at a lower price for sale for weeks without a single sell.<br><br>That said, there's one well known shortcut.  Titan potions, added in Luclin, are trivial at 180 and cost 10.5pp to make.  For comparison's sake, Adrenaline Tap costs 57.8pp to make and trivials at 170.  The first potion cheaper than Titan is Purity, and it trivials at 103.  Another, much lower level shortcut I've found will get you to 36 much cheaper than the usual SoW route.  Check the bazaar for russet oxide, evergreen leaf, and charcoal.  I can usually find a bunch of them for 1pp or under.  Combine any (any one, not all 3) with an empty vial and a water flash, both are cheap as dirt.  It's far, far cheaper than SoW potions to gain skill in, but doesn't result in anything very valuable.  However, you fail the SoW potions so much anyway it's overall cheaper this way.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
